---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="About — As-Built Company"
  description="A California-based 3D scanning team focused on getting accurate existing-conditions data into the hands of the people who need to build from it."
>
  <section class="hero hero-compact">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="eyebrow">About</div>
      <h1>Accurate data. <span class="accent">Honest partnership.</span></h1>
      <p class="lead">We&rsquo;re a California-based 3D scanning team focused on getting accurate existing-conditions data into the hands of the people who need to build from it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container prose">
      <h2>What we do</h2>
      <p>
        We capture buildings, interiors, and sites with survey-grade 3D laser scanners and 360&deg; cameras, then produce the
        drawings, models, and virtual tours that architects, contractors, facility managers, and property owners actually use.
      </p>
      <p>
        Every renovation, retrofit, or coordination effort starts with the same question: what&rsquo;s really there?
        The original drawings rarely match. Field measurements are slow and partial. We deliver a complete, accurate record
        of existing conditions in days, not weeks &mdash; so the rest of the project moves faster and with fewer surprises.
      </p>

      <h2>How we work</h2>
      <p>
        We use mobile-mapping scanners like the Leica BLK2GO for fast site capture and Insta360 cameras for 360&deg; walkthroughs.
        Scans are processed in-house, registered to control points where required, and delivered in the format your team needs &mdash;
        whether that&rsquo;s a Revit model, a stack of AutoCAD plans, an E57 point cloud, or a shareable virtual tour.
      </p>

      <h2>Who we work with</h2>
      <p>
        Architects, general contractors, property owners, real estate professionals, facility managers, engineers, and design teams.
        Project sizes range from single-unit residential to multi-floor commercial.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Team section -->
  <section class="section-surface">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-title-centered">
        <span class="eyebrow">Our Team</span>
        <h2>The people behind the scans.</h2>
        <p>A small, hands-on team. You talk directly with the people who scan, process, and deliver your project.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-2" style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto;">
        <div class="team-card">
          <div class="avatar-large">JC</div>
          <h3>Jonathan Chen</h3>
          <span class="role">Founder · Reality Capture Lead</span>
          <p>[Bio placeholder — add a 2&ndash;3 sentence intro covering background, certifications, and what Jonathan personally handles on projects.]</p>
        </div>
        <div class="team-card">
          <div class="avatar-large">+</div>
          <h3>[Team Member]</h3>
          <span class="role">[Role · e.g. Processing &amp; Modeling]</span>
          <p>[Bio placeholder — add a 2&ndash;3 sentence intro for the second team member.]</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Values -->
  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-title-centered">
        <span class="eyebrow">Our Values</span>
        <h2>What we believe</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <div class="icon-card">
          <div class="icon">◎</div>
          <h3>Accuracy first</h3>
          <p>Data quality is non-negotiable. Every deliverable is verified against control before it leaves our hands.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="icon-card">
          <div class="icon">⏵</div>
          <h3>Speed when it matters</h3>
          <p>Construction doesn&rsquo;t wait. We move at the pace your project demands without cutting corners.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="icon-card">
          <div class="icon">⊜</div>
          <h3>Straight answers</h3>
          <p>If a scope isn&rsquo;t the right fit, we&rsquo;ll say so. We&rsquo;d rather lose a job than oversell one.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Equipment -->
  <section class="section-surface">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-title-centered">
        <span class="eyebrow">Our Equipment</span>
        <h2>Survey-grade tools.</h2>
        <p>We invest in the equipment that delivers reliable, defensible data &mdash; not the cheapest option that fits the day&rsquo;s job.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <div class="icon-card">
          <div class="icon">◆</div>
          <h3>Leica BLK2GO</h3>
          <span class="accuracy-badge">2&ndash;4mm accuracy · 700,000 pts/sec</span>
          <p>Handheld mobile-mapping scanner used for fast, complete interior and exterior capture. SLAM-based registration keeps scans coherent without external targets in most environments.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="icon-card">
          <div class="icon">◉</div>
          <h3>Insta360 Pro Series</h3>
          <span class="accuracy-badge">8K stitched 360&deg; capture</span>
          <p>Professional 360&deg; cameras used for shareable virtual walkthroughs. Stitched and stop-tagged in-house for clean tour delivery.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-strip">
        <div class="text">
          <h3>Let&rsquo;s talk about your project</h3>
          <p>Tell us what you&rsquo;re working on and we&rsquo;ll show you how we can help.</p>
        </div>
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn">Get in Touch <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
